observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:
The Inventory Committee to prepare a systematic and well-planned physical inventory taking and prepare the corresponding Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) and ensure that all the necessary data are provided thereon;
The Municipal Accountant to reconcile the variance between the book value per lapsing schedule of PPE and that presented in the Statement of Financial Position.

We recommended for the Municipal Mayor the following courses of action:
Require the Human Resource and Management Officer to assess existing Organization Structure so that the ideal number of Plantilla personnel will be established and submit a report with recommendations thereon to the LCE for approval by the appropriate bodies;
Instruct the HRMO to create policies and guidelines to address the issue on necessity and propriety of hiring JOs/COS taking into consideration the existing regular employees; and
Direct the HRMO to limit the hiring of personnel under JO/COS to those extremely necessary and deploy only to offices that are actually in need of their services;
Oblige Jos/COS to submit relevant identification documents and clearances;
Instruct the HRMO that in addition to those information already in the memorandum to the JOs/COS, a specific or well-defined task to be performed by the JO/COS personnel should also be stated, and ensure receipt thereof by the JO personnel concerned.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal
Accountant to:
a. Prepare the monthly Bank Reconciliation Statements for December
31, 2019 using the Bank Statement balance as of the same period;
b. Draw Journal Entry Voucher to record the identified unrecorded
book reconciling items and submit the same to the Audit Team;
c. Draw JEV to revert to cash the amounts of staled checks;
d. Submit the Bank Statements for all the depository accounts; and
e. Prepare monthly the Bank Reconciliation Statements for all bank
accounts.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant to:
Prepare and submit the bank reconciliation statements with the bank statement and copies of paid checks as prescribed under  Section 74 of PD 1445 and COA Circular No. 96-011;
Analyze the discrepancies noted between the book and bank confirmed balances;
Make necessary adjustments in the cancellation of stale checks and record the transaction as Account Payable to reflect the correct balances of the cash accounts.

We recommend that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Engineer/BAC Chairman to ensure that:
A list of the Municipality’s programs/projects and activities, inclusive of those for implementation and non-infrastructure projects is submitted to the Audit Team at the beginning of the year;
Relevant information regarding the PPAs of the Municipality be posted in signboards or black/bulletin boards  following the provisions of the cited Circular;
The Audit Team be informed that the appropriate project signboards and/or notices have been  posted  within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/activity; and
Maintain updated Project Status based on the data sourced from the monthly monitoring report prepared by Municipality.
During the exit conference, the Municipal Engineer and the MPDC agreed with the observations and promised to comply with the recommendations.
